                <h1>Tiffany & Co.: A Legacy of Luxury and Elegance</h1>
                <p>Tiffany & Co. was founded in 1837 by Charles Lewis Tiffany and John B. Young in New York City. Originally a stationery and fancy goods store, it quickly gained fame for its exquisite jewelry. In 1848, Tiffany introduced the first American-made diamond engagement ring. Today, it remains synonymous with luxury and timeless elegance.</p>
